      • testMemMapCleared

        public void testMemMapCleared()
                       throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Test that in scarce memory conditions, the memory map is expunged of otherwise unreferenced entries as expected. NOTE: this test may be especially fragile with regard to GC/timing issues; relies on timely finalization, which is never guaranteed by JVM/GC. For example, it is so sensitive to CPU speed that a Thread.sleep(1000) succeeds when my laptop is plugged in, but fails when it is on battery!
        抛出:
        java.lang.InterruptedException
